The President of the United States met with Cuban-American leaders at the White House to discuss his upcoming trip to Cuba. The President reviewed the efforts to normalize relations with Cuba and highlighted recent regulatory changes that would make it easier for Americans to travel to Cuba and engage with the Cuban people. He emphasized that improving the lives of the Cuban people, including access to opportunity, connectivity, and human rights, is a central focus of the policy. The President also mentioned that he will continue to consult with Cuban-Americans, who represent shared values and aspirations for a better future. The meeting was attended by various individuals, including business leaders, faith leaders, and civil society advocates.